This paper deals with the detection of fast flux service networks (FFSNs) using data mining on passive DNS traffic. FFSNs are commonly used for illegal online services, making this paper relevant to the computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The proposed algorithm also involves mathematical and data mining approaches, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the algorithm over an enterprise network, which could be relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
